OL,3,CWales' environmental regulator is
OL,4,C'missing in action' as ex-employees
OL,5,Cspeak out
OL,7,FTwo former employees at Natural
OL,8,FResources Wales have come forward to
OL,9,Fwhistleblow about their experiences
OL,10,Fworking for the environmental
OL,11,Fregulator.
OL,13,FDr Emma Wiik, an ecological scientist,
OL,14,Fsays inaction and bureaucracy at the
OL,15,Forganisation had a depleting impact on
OL,16,Fher life, while another former
OL,17,Femployee who recently left said it's
OL,18,F"demoralising" seeing their field not
OL,19,Fgiven priority and resourcing.
