OL,3,CWales' environmental regulator is
OL,4,C'missing in action' as ex-employees
OL,5,Cspeak out
OL,7,FMr Thomas says that an increased
OL,8,Fpresence by NRW staff, and tougher
OL,9,Fpenalties, would deter polluters in
OL,10,Fthe future.
OL,12,FNatural Resources Wales has prosecuted
OL,13,Fcompanies 215 times since 2016, with
OL,14,Ffines of up to #2.6million. Overall,
OL,15,Fthe number of prosecutions has fallen
OL,16,Fover the years, while enforcement
OL,17,Faction such as 'warning' and 'advice
OL,18,Fand guidance' has increased.
