OL,3,CWales' environmental regulator is
OL,4,C'missing in action' as ex-employees
OL,5,Cspeak out
OL,7,FRegarding the workforce, Ms Pillman
OL,8,Fsaid they "always go the extra mile
OL,9,Ffor the people and places" and that
OL,10,F"ensuring their well-being in the face
OL,11,Fof constant scrutiny and criticism is
OL,12,Fof the utmost importance".
OL,14,FShe added that they are committed to
OL,15,Fkeeping people and nature safe from
OL,16,Fthe impacts of environmental incidents
OL,17,Fand to enforcing the rules to minimise
OL,18,Fpollution. This includes continuing to
OL,19,Fregulate water companies, like Welsh
OL,20,FWater, who they have downgraded from a
OL,21,Fthree-star company, to two.
